OON will our regal structures leave small space Of acres for the ploughshare 3 while we make Our fish-ponds broader than the Lucrine lake, And the unmarried plane-tree takes the place

Of vine-wed elms z soon shrubs ancl flowers will blow, And with a copious fragrance fill the air From beds of violets and myrtles where

Soon will the laurel-trees exclude the rays Of the too fervid sun. It was not thus Under the auspices of Romulus,
